'''''Star Wars Galaxies: Trials of Obi-Wan''''' was the third expansion pack for the [[Star Wars video games#Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|MMORPG]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]''. It was announced on [[August 19]], [[2005]] and released on [[November 1]], 2005.

==Contents==
This expansion added the ground planet of [[Mustafar/Legends|Mustafar]] to the game, and was designed to [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capitalism capitalize] on the DVD release of [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'']] and its final fight sequence between [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]], which was set on the same planet. ''Trials of Obi-Wan'' includes more than 50 new quests, from rescue missions to the exploration of a crashed [[Hammerhead-class cruiser|Republic cruiser]]. Many quests also revolve around the return of [[HK-47]] from ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'', whom players can kill for a quest. The expansion also allows players to interact with the ghost of Obi-Wan Kenobi to help him "[[Mission on Mustafar|correct an imbalance]] in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]]" present on Mustafar. High-level quest rewards include the ability to find a [[Lava crystal/Legends|fiery red crystal]] found only on the volcanic planet that creates a lava-like [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]]. No new space sector was added with this expansion.

